IRS990.MissionDesc: PENINSULA YOUTH ORCHESTRA SEEKS AND TRAINS YOUNG PEOPLE TO ENJOY THE MANY BENEFITS OF MUSIC-MAKING IN THE CONTEXT OF A STRING ORCHESTRA. THE PROGRAM BALANCES NURTURE WITH RIGOR AND COMPASSION WITH EXCELLENCE AND IS OPEN TO ALL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ORGANIZATION AMENDING FORM 990 RETURN TO CORRECT ERRORS IN FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OF PRIOR YEARS. THE WHOLE RETURN NEEDED TO BE AMENDED.

CHANGES TO PROGRAM SERVICES BROUGHT ABOUT BY THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC: 1 STUDENTS AND CONDUCTORS ATTENDING IN-PERSON PRACTICE SESSIONS OBSERVED SOCIAL DISTANCING AND HAND SANITATION PROTOCOLS; 2 ALL COMMON-TOUCH SURFACES SANITIZED AFTER EACH IN-PERSON SESSION; 3 PROGRAM SERVICES WERE ALSO PROVIDED REMOTELY BY WAY OF A VIRTUAL MEETING PLATFORM; 4 MUSIC SESSIONS FOR BEGINNERS WERE SUSPENDED WHILE PRE-INTERMEDIATE AND INTERMEDIATE STUDENTS PRACTICED MUSIC LESSONS TOGETHER; 5 CONCERT PERFORMANCES SUSPENDED; AND 6 WEEK-LONG SUMMER STRING CAMP SUSPENDED.
DRAFT FORM 990 DISTRIBUTED TO BOARD OF DIRECTORS VIA E-MAIL FOR REVIEW AND COMMENT.
GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS WERE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC DURING THE TAX YEAR UPON REQUEST.
